commits.message: Kea / Dhcp - DHCPv4 replacement [https://github.com/opnsense/core/issues/6971], add Auto collect option data checkbox on the subnet. Our current default (legacy) scenario is to use the configured interface addresss as gateway and primary dns, but since we don't want to complicate the templates and make the choice explicit, we're adding an option to auto-collect and persist on configuration save/apply. This commit auto updates selected option data fields on request with the first matching address for the requested subnet found in ifconfig.

issue.title: Input Boolean Renaming Not Altering Name
issue.body: ### The problem When renaming an `input_boolean` entity ID and Name through the GUI the Name parameter does not update in the GUI. This is not a big issue, and has a simple workaround (creating a new helper), but it would be nice for me (and likely others) if the helper name were updated in the GUI. The screenshot below was taken after clicking UPDATE in the helper Settings and making the change. ![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/135544864/963a9ae6-fd6c-4e4a-9931-3b968bc27ed7) As shown in the screenshot above: The Name has been changed to `livingroom_motion_override` The entity ID has been changed to `input_boolean.livingroom_mition_override` But as indicated at the header of the GUI popup, the UI shows the helper as `livingroom_presence_lights_toggle` (the original name for the helper. When viewing Helpers in the Settings section of HA, it shows the updated Entity ID, but not the Name: ![image](https://github.com/home-assistant/core/assets/135544864/4fad0560-c3d5-4acc-aa0e-0c320ea65a60) I have ctrl-f5 refreshed my browser, and logged in and out of HA. The UI mismatch shows in both the desktop web app, and the iOS mobile app. If you need any more details, or logs etc (or which would would be useful) please let me know. And I would image this issue shouldn't be treated as a high priority :). TIA. Richard ### What version of Home Assistant Core has the issue? core-2023.11.1 ### What was the last working version of Home Assistant Core? _No response_ ### What type of installation are you running? Home Assistant OS ### Integration causing the issue Input Boolean helper integration ### Link to integration documentation on our website https://www.home-assistant.io/integrations/input_boolean/ ### Diagnostics information _No response_ ### Example YAML snippet _No response_ ### Anything in the logs that might be useful for us? _No response_ ### Additional information _No response_
